In the AsynchronousTableViewer, the dispose method is written as follows:

    public synchronized void dispose() {
    	fTable.dispose();
    	fTableEditor.dispose();
        super.dispose();
    }  

When the table editor is disposed, its parent table is already disposed.  In the table editor's dispose method:

The method does the following check:
if (this.column > -1 && this.column < table.getColumnCount()){

Since the table is already disposed, we run into a widget disposed exception.

On windows when the dispose call is made, this.column equals to -1.  It seems like the column value could equal to zero on Linux GTK and hence we run into this exception.  This causes it to do the #getColumnCount check and will run into the widget disposed exception.
